
RabbitMQ Puppet Module
======================

This module is Debian/Ubuntu Specific, Tested only on Ubuntu running
Alestic Maverick (10.10) image on AWS.

This module adds RabbitMQ Apt Repository to /etc/apt/sources.list and
installs Latest Stable RabbitMQ Server package.

Refer : http://www.rabbitmq.com/debian.html#apt

Based On : https://github.com/portertech/puppet-mongodb


Installation
============

* cd /etc/puppet/modules/ && git clone git://github.com/greenmang0/puppet-rabbitmq.git rabbitmq
* Make sure that you have "path" for "exec" in your defaults, something like
     Exec { path => "/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin" }
  in the /etc/puppet/manifests/site.pp file.

* Include rabbitmq class in your nodes where you want to have it installed.

